subject: Support configuring bmcweb (HTTPS) service
commitMessage:
Support configuring bmcweb (HTTPS) service

This patch adds support for setting bmcweb service port via redfish
using service_util. Note that changing the enable status of bmcweb is
not allowed to prevent DoS attack, and users should not be able to
disable ther interface they're currently using by design.

Tested:
* PATCH HTTPS.Port in /redfish/v1/Managers/bmc/NetworkProtocol, bmcweb
  will listen on the new port in about 15 seconds.
* PATCH HTTPS.ProtocolEnabled returns PropertyUnknown error.

Change-Id: I1e8407266eedc6321a7ef3d0f8836b2e548931e4
Signed-off-by: Jiaqing Zhao <jiaqing.zhao@intel.com>

Disabling the service you're currently communicating over can lead to DOS attacks, and in the past, we've made the statement that a user should not be able to disable the interface they're currently using.
Removed PATCH HTTPS.ProtocolEnabled support
This is not enough of a tested statement.
Done
Why so long?  I would've expected this to be less than 1 second.

The author of service-config-manager designs a 15s window for incoming changes (each DBus set is considered as one change), changes submitted in the following 15s from the first change will be merged and applied together in a single systemd reload. He says decreasing the 15s window time will causes multiple service restarts and may cause loss of data.
That seems way too high to me (I would've expected 1 second), but in this context ACK.

Can this code use the new multi-depth parsing in readJsonPatch?

Similar to here:

https://gerrit.openbmc-project.xyz/c/openbmc/bmcweb/+/51553


Ideally line 338 would be something like

json_util::readJsonPatch(req, asyncResp->res,
"NTP", ntp,
"HostName", newHostName,
"IPMI/ProtocolEnabled", ipmiEnabled,
"IPMI/Port", ipmiPortNumber,
"SSH/ProtocolEnabled", sshEnabled,
"SSH/Port", sshPortNumber,
"HTTPS/ProtocolEnabled", httpsEnabled,
"HTTPS/Port", httpsPortNumber,
)



Was the above something you were aware of?  I'm not necessarily going to require that pattern, but it would simplify this function a lot.
I was unaware of this change. I am going to adopt it as it makes the PATCH hander much easier to code.
Done
